6. Shell Scripts
6.1 Script 1 – System Identity Report

This script displays system information such as username, kernel version, uptime, distribution, and date. It helps in understanding system configuration.

6.2 Script 2 – Package Inspector

This script checks whether Python is installed and displays its version and package details using conditional statements.

6.3 Script 3 – Disk and Permission Auditor

This script analyzes system directories and displays permissions, ownership, and size, helping in understanding system structure.

6.4 Script 4 – Log File Analyzer

This script searches for a keyword (e.g., “error”) in system log files, counts occurrences, and displays recent entries.

Observation:

Not all matches represent actual errors, as some may include the keyword within package names. This highlights a limitation of keyword-based analysis.

6.5 Script 5 – Manifesto Generator

This script takes user input and generates a personalized open-source manifesto stored in a text file.

