9. Conclusion

This project provided practical knowledge of open-source software, Linux systems, and shell scripting. It demonstrated how Python can be used effectively in an open-source environment and how Linux tools can be utilized for system analysis and automation.

The use of WSL simplified the setup process by allowing Linux functionality within Windows. Overall, the project improved understanding of open-source philosophy, system operations, and scripting techniques.
